PIDIV - Arithmetic Utilities

OVERVIEW

Three programs for arithmetic operations:

  divide    - integer division with remainder (x86-64 asm)
  dividePi  - pi / divisor with FPU precision (x86-64 asm)
  piCalc    - calculate pi to N digits (C)

REQUIREMENTS

  - GNU Assembler (as) 2.30+
  - GNU Linker (ld) 2.30+
  - GCC
  - Linux x86-64

BUILDING

  $ make

USAGE

  $ ./divide
  14 R 2

  $ ./dividePi
  0.448798951

  $ ./piCalc
  3.1415926535...

CONFIGURATION

divide.s / dividePi.s:
  dividend: .long 100    # Numerator
  divisor:  .long 7      # Denominator

piCalc.c:
  #define PRECISION 100  # Decimal places

CLEAN

  $ make clean

LIMITATIONS

  - Division by zero causes SIGFPE
  - piCalc precision limited by memory

AUTHOR

None.

